<subSubSection pageId="25" pageNumber="26" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="25.[151,1437,151,514]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,328,226,252]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
This species can be distinguished easily from its congeners by the ductus bursae distinctly enlarged into ovate before the colliculum, and the swollen part is nearly as large as the corpus bursae.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
