<subSubSection pageId="25" pageNumber="26" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="25.[151,1437,151,514]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,320,338,364]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[329,578,338,363]" class="Insecta" family="Crambidae" genus="Scoparia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="yamanakai">
<emphasis box="[329,578,338,363]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Scoparia yamanakai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was recorded by 
<bibRefCitation author="Song" box="[793,1018,338,364]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" refString="Song, S. M. &amp; He, M. S. (1997) Lepidoptera: Pyralidae. In: Yang, X. K. (ed.), Insect of Three Gorges of Changjiang, vol. 2. Chongqing Press. Chongqing. 1096 - 1220 pp." type="journal article" year="1997">
Song &amp; He (
<number box="[946,1009,338,364]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" value="1997.0">1997</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
based on the four male specimens collected in Hubei and Sichuan provinces of 
<collectingCountry box="[724,799,376,402]" name="China" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">China</collectingCountry>
(
<number box="[821,835,376,402]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" value="1.0">1</number>
<number box="[844,866,375,401]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" value="3.0">3</number>
, Shiping, Fengdu, Sichuan Province, 
<quantity box="[1349,1432,376,402]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.1" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" unit="m" value="610.0">610 m</quantity>
, 
<date box="[151,280,413,439]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" value="1994-09-10">
<number box="[151,181,413,439]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" value="10.0">10</number>
.ix. 
<number box="[215,280,413,439]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" value="1994.0">1994</number>
</date>
; 
<number box="[293,308,413,439]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" value="3.0">3</number>
<number box="[316,338,412,438]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" value="3.0">3</number>
, Longmenhe, Xingshan, Hubei Province, 
<quantity box="[859,951,413,439]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.35" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" unit="m" value="1350.0">1350 m</quantity>
, 
<date box="[964,1102,413,439]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" value="1994-07-13">
<number box="[964,993,413,439]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" value="13.0">13</number>
.vii. 
<number box="[1036,1102,413,439]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" value="1994.0">1994</number>
</date>
). Judging from the figure of male genitalia (
<bibRefCitation author="Song" box="[334,649,450,476]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" refString="Song, S. M. &amp; He, M. S. (1997) Lepidoptera: Pyralidae. In: Yang, X. K. (ed.), Insect of Three Gorges of Changjiang, vol. 2. Chongqing Press. Chongqing. 1096 - 1220 pp." type="journal article" year="1997">
Song &amp; He 
<number box="[479,542,450,476]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" value="1997.0">1997</number>
: fig. 
<number box="[602,649,450,476]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" value="145.0">145</number>
</bibRefCitation>
), this could be a misidentification, but we are unable to recognize which species it is by the simple drawing.
</paragraph>
